{
  "_schema": {
    "version": "1.0",
    "description": "Authoritative record of all inter-station dispatches. Tracks routing, delivery, and cryptographic integrity for every message sent over the ring network. Designed to support future scenarios including partial topology disconnection, message suppression, and relay tampering.",
    "notes": [
      "Timestamp IDs reference tracking/timestamps.json — never hardcode dates",
      "Topology snapshots record link state at a point in time; dispatches reference the active snapshot",
      "Integrity model: origin station signs content; relay stations append receipts; recipients verify",
      "A relay can suppress or delay a message but cannot forge a different origin signature",
      "Selective forwarding (sending in one ring direction but not the other) is detectable by comparing delivery confirmations but not preventable"
    ]
  },

